headline: KEY Q2 Deep Dive: Commercial Loan Momentum and Deposit Discipline Drive Results
summary: Regional banking company KeyCorp (NYSE:KEY) reported revenue ahead of Wall Street’s expectations in Q2 CY2025, with sales up 20% year on year to $1.83 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $0.35 per share was in line with analysts’ consensus estimates.
